VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \B--inspect(?:-brk)?(?:=\S+)?\b
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:--inspect|--inspect-brk && MISSING:development|localhost|127\.0\.0\.1|test
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects Node.js debug inspector flags that may expose a remotely reachable debug endpoint.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Node Inspector Exposed via --inspect.
